==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syntonizer
<hw>Syn"to*niz`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>One that syntonizes; specif., a device consisting essentially of a
variable inductance coil and condenser with a pair of adjustable spark
balls, for attuning the time periods of antennae in wireless telegraphy
(called also <altname><col><b>syntonizing
coil</b></col></altname>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syntony</ent>⟦br⟧
